Text:
Thank you.

@sopasux: the first version had a corrupted audio stream and therefore the two tracks, 5.1 and stereo were dumped and the TV-rip stereo audio track was spliced in.  If you are building a collection with quality standards, such as everything is 720p with 5.1 audio, having one episode that is only in stereo just doesn't fit with the rest.

I for one really appreciate this updated/fixed/proper version being posted, both by the poster, and whoever cares enough to put it into the iTunes store.  If you think it is a total waste of time, you wasted your time commenting about it if it doesn't matter to you.
